<div class="notes" style="float:left;padding:15px;width:auto;font-weight:bold;">
	<h4>About <i>CM Engine</i>:</h4>
<p>
	<i>CM Engine</i> translates digital images of rectangular plates that contain gridded colonies into quantitative data. It currently contains 4 analysis modes to ensure accurate measurements no matter how cells are deposited onto the agar. It also has multiple error correction algorithms built in to ensure accurate quantifications. <i>CM Engine</i> is licensed as an open source macro for the freely available NIH program, ImageJ. If you use <i>CM Engine</i> or any other tool within the ScreenMill suite, please site:
</p>
<p  style="padding-top:5px;">
	<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20584323" class="ext_link">Dittmar JC, Reid RJ, Rothstein R. "ScreenMill: a freely available software suite for growth measurement, analysis and visualization of high-throughput screen data." BMC BioInformatics. 2010.</a>
</p>
</div>
<div class="theRest" style="clear:both">
<strong><u>Download:</u></strong>
<ul>
	<li>The <i>CM Engine</i> software is GPL licensed and available on SourceForge <a href='http://cm-engine.sourceforge.net' class="ext_link" title="SourceForge" >here.</a></li>
	<li><%= link_to "Mirror of <i>CM Engine v1.64</i> for ImageJ <strong>v1.47+</strong>".html_safe, "#{ENV['RAILS_RELATIVE_URL_ROOT']}/cm_engine/cm engine_ImageJ1.64.txt" %></li>
